  <title><custom ref="synthesis-leccion-titulo"/></title>
  <title component="profesor"><nbsp/>(20 mins)</title>

  <p>[@@@@@@@@@] The end of this lesson is a good place for students to take a moment and reflect on the learning of the past four lessons. Some questions to guide the discussion:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>
    <p>
      <q>Describe some ways to understand how a situation can be represented mathematically.</q>
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <q>What have you learned about equations that surprised you?</q>
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <q>Share your thoughts about using diagrams to help understand relationships. Where have you seen diagrams used earlier this year? Where were they most helpful to you? Least helpful?</q>
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      <q>Describe any connections you see between the types of diagrams used in the last four lessons.</q>
    </p>
  </li>
  </ul>

</subsubsection>



